<HEADLINE>
FT  26 NOV 94 / Weekend Money (Companies): Directors' dealings
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By VIVIEN MACDONALD, Inside Track
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
The largest transaction of the week was at Gerrard and National Holdings, a
financial house that announced interim results on October 27 showing a good
increase on the same period last year, writes Vivien MacDonald of The Inside
Track.
Chairman Robert Williamson was also upbeat in his message to shareholders.
For personal reasons, however, executive director Mark Davies has sold
359,000 shares at 470p.
Hewden Stuart, a Glasgow-based plant hire company, announced improved
interims last month. The sale by Ronald Stuart, deputy chairman, leaves him
with more than 750,000 shares.
