<HEADLINE>
FT  25 NOV 94 / World Stock Markets: De Beers advances 3% as Namibia takes
stake in diamond operations
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Equities finished firmer, although trade was cautious in the absence of a
lead from the US. Brokers said most of the overseas buying had come from the
UK.
The overall index rose 67.4 to 5,866.8 after a 109-point decline on
Wednesday; industrials put on 83 at 6,949.9; and the golds index was 20.4
higher at 2,067.7 after a static afternoon performance.
De Beers advanced R2.75 to R95.75 as the group announced that the Namibian
government had taken a 50 per cent stake in its diamond mining operations
there.
Anglos was unchanged at R234 and Minorco moved ahead R1.65 to R98.15. SAB
recovered some of Wednesday's loss, improving R2 to R99, while Barlows
appreciated R1 to R34.25.
