<PROFILE>_AN-EKYELAGOFT</PROFILE>
<DATE>941125
</DATE>
<HEADLINE>
FT  25 NOV 94 / Commodities and Agriculture: Diamond market undermined by
Russians says De Beers chief
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Russia continued to 'undermine the delicate equilibrium and confidence
necessary for the diamond industry,' said Mr Julian Ogilvie Thompson, De
Beers' chairman, last night. 'Competing interests (in Russia) have not
adhered to the necessary disciplines and have been leaking diamonds on to
the open market in contravention of the contracts with the Central Selling
Organisation,' he complained. This placed Russia 'in the role of competitor
with the other diamond producers'. But De Beers had dealt with similar
problems in the past 60 years 'and on each occasion the CSO and the industry
have emerged stronger than before'.
</TEXT>
<XX>
Companies:-
</XX>
<CO>Central Selling Organisation.
</CO>
<XX>
Countries:-
</XX>
