FT  25 NOV 94 / World Commodities Prices: Wool
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Prices at auctions this week were generally firm, and wool was in
sufficiently good demand for clearances to the trade to be good. There was
no clear rise in the market, however, and without this incentive business is
very quiet. The usual pattern is of better business in November, but this
month has been quiet throughout Europe. Order books were filled quite far
ahead two or three months ago, also unusually timed, so there is no special
anxiety about activity at present.
