<HEADLINE>
FT  25 NOV 94 / International Capital Markets: Tisa loan in general
syndication
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By REUTER and MARTIN BRICE
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
A Dollars 1.1bn syndicated loan for Spain's Telefonica Internacional (Tisa),
a subsidiary of Telefonica de Espana, has been launched into general
syndication, Reuter reports.
The seven-year loan, which carries a spread of 27.5 basis points over London
inter-bank offered rate (Libor), is a refinancing of a Dollars 1bn
seven-month bridging facility signed in May to buy two Peruvian
telecommunications companies.
Arrangers of the syndicated loan are ABN-Amro Bank and Banco de Negocios
Argentaria, together with underwriters Bank of Tokyo, Fuji Bank, Banque
Nationale de Paris and Bank of America.
An Dollars 850m revolving credit for Saga Petroleum, the Norwegian energy
group, has also been launched into general syndication, writes Martin Brice.
Arrangers are ABN Amro, Deutsche and Barclays, with co-arrangers Christiania
Bank and Den norske Bank.
The seven-year loan is priced at 30 basis points over Libor for years one to
five and 35 over for years six and seven, with undrawn facilities at 15
basis points for years one to five and 17 1/2 for years six and seven.
Underwriting for the Kingdom of Sweden's Dollars 5bn syndicated loan should
be complete by the middle of next week, said Ms Christine Holm of the
Swedish National Debt Office.
</TEXT>
