<HEADLINE>
FT  25 NOV 94 / International Company News: Barings raises Dollars 180m for
east Europe fund
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By NICHOLAS DENTON
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
The Barings group of the UK has raised Dollars 180m for a new investment
vehicle for the former Soviet Union, taking the pool of funds targeted at
eastern Europe to more than Dollars 1bn.
The First NIS Regional Fund announced yesterday that it had indications of
Dollars 160m of equity commitments and a further Dollars 20m of guaranteed
debt financing.
Baring Brothers, the merchant banking subsidiary, sponsored the placing and
Baring International Investment Management is to manage the fund.
The fund has come to the market at the same time as Invesco's East Europe
Development Fund, which last week announced it had raised Dollars 75m,
taking its net asset value to Dollars 170m. First NIS Regional Fund will be
one of the largest three east European funds, alongside EEDF and CS First
Boston's Central European Growth Fund, which raised Dollars 200m on its
launch earlier this year.
Barings already manages the Barings Emerging Europe Trust and it issued and
placed the latest EEDF transaction.
Core investors in First NIS Regional Fund are the European Bank for
Reconstruction and Development and the International Finance Corporation.
The EBRD committed Dollars 20m.
Barings, like most managers of funds in the region, said it was aiming for
long-term capital growth. However, it said it expected a large proportion of
the fund's investments would be unlisted or, if listed, illiquid.
</TEXT>
