<HEADLINE>
FT  25 NOV 94 / UK Company News: Kiln Capital raises Pounds 25m in placing
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By RALPH ATKINS, Insurance Correspondent
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Kiln Capital, a planned new listed company investing in Lloyd's of London,
has raised Pounds 25m via a share placing.
Kiln plans to invest exclusively in insurance syndicates managed by the RJ
Kiln managing agency, unlike many other Lloyd's investment companies which
have spread funds across a range of syndicates. Dealings are expected to
start on December 1.
The company has also made an offer to some Names to subscribe for up to 2m
ordinary shares at 100p each.
Plans for corporate investment in Lloyd's have been affected this year by
the lacklustre performance of existing corporate vehicles.
Mr Colin Murray, chairman of RJ Kiln, said he was 'delighted' with the
response to date.
</TEXT>
