<HEADLINE>
FT  25 NOV 94 / UK Company News: Linden in Pounds 16m reverse takeover of
Edmond
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Linden, an unquoted housebuilder which operates in Surrey, Sussex and
Cheshire is acquiring Edmond Holdings, the housebuilder, in a reverse
takeover worth Pounds 16.1m.
Edmond, which operates in east Midlands, East Anglia, Yorkshire and
Humberside, is issuing 78.8m ordinary shares, representing 60.7 per cent of
its enlarged share capital.
Mr Andrew Sells, Linden's chairman, will become non-executive chairman of
Edmond and Mr Philip Davies, Linden's chief executive, will become chief
executive of Edmond.
Dealings in Edmond have been suspended and as Linden does not have a
three-year trading record, application will be made for Edmond's admission
to the USM.
</TEXT>
